abstract: George P. McCulloch, Esq., a distinguished citizen; of New--Jersey, died in Morristown on Tuesday, aged 83. He was born in Bombay, his father being a Scotch officer in the East India service. He was emplayed during the first Consulate of Napoleon, in various financial negotiations for the East India Company, and caine to New-York in 1806. He settled soon after at Morristown, where he has since resided.
